	<text xml:lang="la">
		<body>
			<div xml:id="div1" corresp="regest1">
				<p>
					<s n="1" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Gratiam et pacem.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="2" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Signaveram literas priores<note xml:id="fn1" type="footnote" n="1">Oben <ref target="file10913">Nr. 873</ref>.</note> easque tradideram <persName>Erasmo</persName> nostro<note xml:id="fn2" type="footnote" n="2"><persName>Erasmus Schmid</persName>.</note> cum in, mentem venit non infrugiferum futurum, si ea tibi ex opere nostro Paulino nondum perfecto<note xml:id="fn3" type="footnote" n="3">Bullinger, In omnes apostolicas epistolas commentarii, Zürich 1537 (<bibl>HBBibl</bibl> I 84).</note> mitterem, quae scripsi de ratione sacramentorum et eucharistia.</s>
					<s n="3" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Istis vero novum exemplar loqupletavi; in aliis ante annos aliquot aeditis<note xml:id="fn4" type="footnote" n="4">Bullingers Kommentar zum Römerbrief (<bibl>HBBibl</bibl> I 42) war 1533, jener zum ersten Korintherbrief (<bibl>HBBibl</bibl> I 53) 1534 erstmals erschienen.</note> haec per omnia non leges.</s>
					<s n="4" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Lege itaque, quae scripsi fol. 41 usque ad 45, et rursus, quae sunt fol. 204 usque ad 216<note xml:id="fn5" type="footnote" n="5">An den genannten Stellen handelt Bullinger ausführlich über die Sakramente (zu Röm 4, 11f; aaO, S. 41-45) und über die Eucharistie (zu 1Kor 11, 17-34; aaO, S. 202-216).</note>.</s>
					<s n="5" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Planius et melius ego de hoc negotio dicere non possum.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="6" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Vale et haec nostra etiam <persName>Grynaeo</persName> communica aut, si placet, ipsi etiam <persName ref="p18198">Bucero</persName>.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="7" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Tiguri, 4. augusti 1536.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<s n="8" xml:lang="la" type="auto">H. Bullingerus tuus.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<note type="address">[Adresse auf der Rückseite:]</note>
					<s n="9" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Domino <persName>Myconio</persName> suo.</s>
				</p>
			</div>
		</body>
	</text>
